Simple Debugging Techniques in Python
1Ô∏è‚É£ print() Statements (Most Common)
print("Reached here")
print(x)


Used to:

Check program flow

See variable values

2Ô∏è‚É£ Read Error Messages (Traceback)

Always read from bottom to top

Look for:

Error type

File name

Line number

Example:

ZeroDivisionError: division by zero

3Ô∏è‚É£ Use try‚Äìexcept
try:
    x = int(input())
except ValueError:
    print("Invalid input")


Used to:

Catch errors

Prevent crashes

Show friendly messages

4Ô∏è‚É£ Python Debugger (pdb)
